{"agent_id":"79Ig","agent_seq":84,"timestamp":"2026-07-22T16:57:27.489549Z","event":{"type":"CommentAdded","issue_uuid":"028e84f4-cfd0-45aa-8aee-b43ec885d803","comment_uuid":"d13e7c01-dbf0-484d-9d4b-f9fe32448634","author":"79Ig","content":"Discovered while working #76. mdatron verify uses VerifyConfig::new() which hardcodes file_globs=['**/*.md']; the CLI never reads the committed .mdatron/config.yaml. So 'mdatron verify --project-root .' walks ALL 54 .claude/*.md + .crosslink/*.md tooling files plus review-log/, not just mdatron's own typed-markdown corpus. It stays clean ONLY because those files currently have valid (or absent) YAML frontmatter — proven fragile: a local .claude/commands/design.md (Claude Code skill file, argument-hint line is not strict YAML) makes verify emit E0001. Impact: #46's self-validate CI gate would break the moment any committed non-corpus .md carries non-YAML frontmatter — and 'verify via its own .mdatron/ config' (#46 acceptance) is not actually honored since config.yaml is inert. FIX: (1) cmd_verify reads .mdatron/config.yaml file_globs (fall back to default when absent); (2) set the committed config.yaml globs to scope the corpus (review-log/**/*.md) so verify validates only mdatron-owned typed-markdown. NOTE: config.yaml is a managed/drift-guarded file (init manifest) but file_globs are inherently project-specific — this resurfaces the config-governance question (adopter-customizable config vs engine-managed). Links #46/#44. Correcting my earlier #46 assessment: I concluded 'default globs scope correctly (glob skips dotdirs)' — that was WRONG; the glob DOES walk dotdirs, it just happened to find valid frontmatter.","created_at":"2026-07-22T16:57:27.474068Z","kind":"note","signed_by":"SHA256:u0VtJEsnHrvNPG5QQKKfDO+Rro/KT/xZqEvahzZTqEA","signature":"U1NIU0lHAAAAAQAAADMAAAALc3NoLWVkMjU1MTkAAAAgOk7MLoVvSEPAWM9VkHKFnHq8O1iEkPSfqY7zLc4I28oAAAARY3Jvc3NsaW5rLWNvbW1lbnQAAAAAAAAABnNoYTUxMgAAAFMAAAALc3NoLWVkMjU1MTkAAABAi177zXJe4rmh0OhyTw2VC66Q