{"agent_id":"79Ig","agent_seq":94,"timestamp":"2026-07-22T17:10:24.428196Z","event":{"type":"CommentAdded","issue_uuid":"85c72705-2c55-4332-bb4d-9616e2ffef82","comment_uuid":"2b86f4c0-773b-4cd1-a2d5-54a77d820748","author":"79Ig","content":"CONSUMER RAISE (vsdd-cli relay 2026-07-22, Raise 1). Passed their ratified scope test (document-anchored, generic), failed their support test, raised here. DEFECT: frontmatter.rs parse() requires content to start exactly '---\\n' (~line 27). A UTF-8 BOM (U+FEFF) prefix or CRLF fence ('---\\r\\n') fails the check -> Ok(None) -> verify's dispatch finds no schema_class (verify.rs ~269-277), no schema and no pattern applies -> the file PASSES THE WALK SILENTLY. Meanwhile vsdd's lenient consumer-side loader (tolerates BOM+CRLF after a review finding) validates the same file — a governed artifact validated by one tool, invisible to the other. The hole sits precisely on Windows-editor provenance (and we ship a windows CI leg — CRLF is in scope). KEY ASYMMETRY: parse FAILURE is loud (E0001, proven live this week); parse ABSENCE is indistinguishable from not-governed. THREE SEPARABLE ASKS: (a) tolerate leading BOM + CRLF fences in parse() — straight fix, this issue's core; (b) loudness option: a file matching a governed glob (or configured must-have-frontmatter glob) that parses Ok(None) reports instead of silently passing — interacts with #77's routing (a route table makes 'routed but frontmatterless' well-defined); needs a new W-code + design language, likely SO-touching; (c) shared fence-edge conformance corpus both projects test against — vsdd contributes: BOM opening, CRLF fences, bare '---' inside a block scalar (BOTH parsers truncate at first bare fence — pin as shared deliberate semantics), empty block, unterminated fence. PLAN: fix (a) with red gates from the (c) corpus cases in one lane; route (b) to a design decision alongside #77's default question.","created_at":"2026-07-22T17:10:24.415850Z","kind":"plan","signed_by":"SHA256:u