{"agent_id":"79Ig","agent_seq":98,"timestamp":"2026-07-22T17:11:06.011454Z","event":{"type":"CommentAdded","issue_uuid":"3cc73526-d8d8-4eb3-9bd3-a7affee9ee90","comment_uuid":"c7216b6d-b368-4a09-a37b-80c075f90c04","author":"79Ig","content":"CONSUMER RAISE (vsdd-cli relay 2026-07-22, Raise 2). FAILURE CLASS: prose in a frontmatter-bearing document restates a count/enumeration the frontmatter carries, and the copies drift. vsdd paid 3x in ONE review cycle ('17 domain prompts' vs 18 on disk; 'seven core domains' vs six; stale 'three OPEN notes') — each caught only by expensive cold-review lenses, none mechanically. Their interim authoring rule's contract text literally says 'until a numeric-claims pattern exists'. ASK: a Layer-2-family primitive flagging numeric literals in body prose that plausibly restate frontmatter facts (collection lengths, count fields). Design fully ours; their suggested conservative first cut: scoped to CONFIGURED FIELD REFERENCES (adopter declares which fields' counts prose may restate), not free inference. They contribute the 3 historical drift cases as fixtures. GENERALITY: any consumer pairing machine frontmatter with human prose has this class. ASSESSMENT: this is the first BODY-PROSE check primitive (current families are frontmatter-only) — a real scope decision against the deliberately-narrowed DSL, but squarely 'document-anchored rules supplied as data' per the ratified identity, and it's cross-representation (frontmatter<->prose) drift, the project's founding failure class (cross-document count drift was bootstrap-validator Class 1!). Route: candidate primitive for the #45 conformance-families design pass; needs SO scope ratification before build. Note the resonance: the bootstrap validator's Class-1 check (count drift vs canonical-counts.yaml) was deleted at #46 — this raise effectively asks for its principled, generic successor inside the engine.","created_at":"2026-07-22T17:11:05.993381Z","kind":"plan","signed_by":"SHA256:u0VtJEsnHrv